  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN136.1-kilavi">uṇarppuvayiṉ vārāvūṭaṟkaṇ <app><lem>talaimakaṉ</lem><rdg wit="#C3 #C7 #C9v #RK">talaimakaṉ taṉ</rdg></app> neñciṟkuc colliyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What HE said to [his] heart during a quarrel before regaining mental clarity.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN136.1">
                <l>maippuṟap puḻukki ṉeykkaṉi veṇcōṟu</l>
                <l>varaiyā vaṇmaiyoṭu puraiyōrp pēṇip</l>
                <l>puḷḷuppuṇarn tiṉiya vākat teḷḷoḷi</l>
                <l>yaṅka ṇiruvicumpu viḷaṅkat tiṅkaḷ</l>
                <l>cakaṭa maṇṭiya tukaṭīr kūṭṭattuk</l>
                <l>kaṭina<supplied>ka</supplied>r puṉaintu kaṭavuṭ pēṇip</l>
                <l>paṭumaṇa muḻavoṭu parūuppaṇai yimiḻa</l>
                <l>vatuvai maṇṇiya makaḷir vituppuṟṟup</l>
                <l>pūkka ṇimaiyōr nōkkupu maṟaiya</l>
                <l>meṉpū vākaip puṉpuṟak kavaṭṭilai</l>
                <l>paḻaṅkaṉṟu kaṟitta payampama laṟukai</l>
                <l>taḻaṅkukural vāṉiṉ ṟalaippeyaṟ kīṉṟa</l>
                <l>maṇṇumaṇi <supplied>ya</supplied>ṉṉa mā<supplied>yi</supplied>taḻp pāvai</l>
                <l>taṇṇaṟu mukaiyoṭu veṇṇūl cūṭṭit</l>
                <l>tūvuṭaip polintu mēvarat tuvaṉṟi</l>
                <l>maḻaipaṭ ṭaṉṉa maṇa<supplied>ṉ</supplied>mali panta</l>
                <l>riḻaiyaṇi ciṟappiṟ peyar<supplied>vi</supplied>yarp pāṟṟit</l>
                <l>tamarnamak kīnta talainā <supplied>ḷi</supplied>ravi</l>
                <l>ṉuvarnīṅka kaṟpiṉem muyiruṭam paṭuvi</l>
                <l>muruṅkāk kaliṅka muḻuvatum vaḷaiip</l>
                <l>perumpuḻuk kuṟṟaniṉ <supplied>pi</supplied>ṟainutaṟ poṟiviya</l>
                <l>ruṟuvaḷi yāṟṟac ciṟuvarai tiṟaveṉa</l>
                <l>vārva neñcamoṭu pōrvai vavvali</l>
                <l>ṉuṟaikaḻi vāḷi ṉuruvupeyarn timaippa</l>
                <l>maṟaitiṟa ṉaṟiyā ḷāki yoyyeṉa</l>
                <l>nāṇiṉa ḷiṟaiñci yōḷē pēṇip</l>
                <l>parūuppakai yāmpaṟ kurūuttoṭai nīvi</l>
                <l>curumpimi rāymalar vēynta</l>
                <l>virumpal kūnta liruṇmaṟai yoḷittē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>Honouring great people with an unbound liberality</l>
                <l>of white rice on which ghee melts with meat from the back of a goat, (1f.)</l>
                <l>as birds unite so as to be auspicious, during the flawless union</l>
                <l>when the moon has entered the cart [constellation]</l>
                <l>so that the dark sky shines there with white light (3-5)</l>
                <l>decorating the protected house, honouring the gods, (6)</l>
                <l>while the large drum buzzes along with the drum for the ensuing marriage, (7)</l>
                <l>after women have made haste to bathe the bride (8)</l>
                <l>[and now] hide while looking on, their flower eyes unblinking, (9)</l>
                <l>putting a white thread with cool fragrant buds (14)</l>
                <l>on the doll [made] of large petals [blue] like polished sapphire, (13)</l>
                <l>brought forth by the rain showered by the sky with thundering voice, (12)</l>
                <l>[and] Aṟukai grass grown thick in a pit, chewed by an older calf, (11)</l>
                <l>with the forked leaves from the low trunk of the soft-flowered Sirissa, (10)</l>
                <l>crowding in desirously, flourishing in pure clothes,</l>
                <l>in the arbour abounding in sand as if rain had fallen, (15f.)</l>
                <l>in the night of the main day when her people gave [her] to us,</l>
                <l>appeasing [her] perspiration trickling because of the decorative weight of the jewels, (17f.)</l>
                <l>when these people left, she who had consented to our life in fidelity</l>
                <l>being enveloped fully in an unsoiled garment, (19f.)</l>
                <l>when I snatched at the covering with ardent heart,</l>
                <l>saying “open up a little so that the approaching wind may cool</l>
                <l>the perspiration in drops on your crescent moon forehead that suffers great heat”, (21-23)</l>
                <l>in a blink [her] form moved, like a sword drawn from the sheath, (24)</l>
                <l>not knowing how to hide, suddenly (25)</l>
                <l>ashamed she bowed, carefully(?) (26)</l>
                <l>stroking off [her] brilliant wreath of big waterlilies in contrasting [colours] (27)</l>
                <l>[and] concealing [her] secrets in the darkness of [her] ample black tresses (29)</l>
                <l>covered by choice blossoms in which bees hummed. (28)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
